descript.abstract: The original (major) watersheds divides were created by a Pedersen Planning Consultants (contracted by American Samoa Environmental Protection Agency) and assigned unique names and numbers determined by the Natural Resource Conservation Service (NRCS). The watersheds of Tutuila and Aunu'u were updated with a digital vector shoreline that was manually digitized from the one-meter panchromatic IKONOS imagery. In addition, coast length, population density and watershed condition data were generated for each watershed and included in the attribute table.
descript.purpose: The Pacific Islands Geographic Information System (GIS) project is a multiyear initiative designed to increase the use of GIS and related spatial technology in the coastal resource management programs of the Terrorities of American Samoa and Guam, the Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands (CNMI), and the State of Hawaii. The project will focus on personnel, training, equipment, software, data, and applications. Where appropriate, other related activities in the region will be incorporated into the effort.

procstep.procdesc:
Shoreline of the watersheds file was updated using digital vectorized shorelines made from 2001 panchromatic IKONOS satellite imagery. Polygons for each watershed were assigned unique names and identification numbers established by NRCS. Coast lengths for each watershed were calculated (meters) and included in the attribute table. Population density statistics were generated for each watershed using 2000 census data. Watershed condition was determined by ASEPA based upon population density.
Known problems: none

dataqual.logic: Coastline updated from linework that was vectorized using one-meter IKONOS imagery. Watershed delineations believed to have been derived from Digital Elevation Model (DEM, updated in 1989) by Pedersen Planning Consultants.
dataqual.complete: These data accurately represented the shoreline at the time of image capture. Watershed delineations consistent with 10 meter contour intervals built from DEM that was created by the United States Geological Survery (USGS).

horizpa.horizpar: Vector shoreline data derived from geo-referenced panchromatic IKONOS satellite imagery with 2.7 meter circular error.

attracc.attraccr: Area, perimeter and acreage statistics generated using XTOOLS software. Coastlengths determined using IKONOS imagery derived digital shoreline. Unique watershed names and numbers supplied by USDA NRCS. Watershed condition determined by ASEPA and based upon population densities generated from 2000 census data.
